  <description type="morphology">Plants robust. Involucres turbinate, 8–12 mm. Phyllaries in 5–7 series, appressed, obtuse, densely strigillose to canescent, eglandular or sparsely glandular; mid 1.2–1.7 mm wide. 2n = 20.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering late Aug–early Nov.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry oak-hickory woodlands;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–1000+ m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ark., Ill., Kans., Ky., La., Miss., Mo., Okla., Tex.</description>
  <number>13a.</number>
  <discussion>Variety patentissimum is found mostly west of the Mississippi River, in the Interior Uplands of the eastern United States. It is similar to the typical variety except for the involucre, which is usually 8–12 mm with more phyllaries in more series. Intermediates occur with var. patens.</discussion>
